metadata.name: Cockcoins #26
metadata.description:
Welcome to the cocktoid currency, Cockcoins! These coins can be redeemed for custom Dickgenerate art. The Dickgenerate art piece will most likely be in the style of Trebonius, which is a piece that has not debuted yet. Additional rules apply, see below:

- You must submit coins with a total of at least 100
-- every coin is worth it's face value times the multiplier from its shape
--- circle = 1
--- square = 2
--- hexagon = 3
-- one set of coins can only be redeemed for one drawing
- You can only request colors that are present within the Cockcoins you submitted
-- submitting one black coin lets you choose any colors (up to 5)
--- you can only fit so many colors into a Dickgenerative art, I will try to be accommodating

Further more, depending on the randomness of the mints I may drop the price of requesting a custom piece. The expected value of the mints is so that 100 is a fair price, but I will adjust accordingly if requests are low.

metadata.name: Maquette #26
metadata.description:
Like a photography of a city maquette with citizens.

Created in javascript / webGL using three.js and pathtracer.
May - June 2022
@arthurmchr

———
Path tracing is an heavy GPU operation.
Depending on the device, it can takes a few seconds to render.
Worked on Chrome and Firefox.

In live mode :
press S to export a PNG of the rendered image.
press P to pause / resume rendering (automatically paused after 100 rendering steps).

metadata.name: AUTOJOURNEYPAINT #254
metadata.description:
An automatic painting journey

AUTOJOURNEYPAINT  uses a series of custom built walkers to make plots with a great variety of properties, including packing gaps, directions and propensity for turning. These plots are then drawn over with varying, incremented pixel brushes.

AUTOJOURNEYPAINT chooses color for itself from a broad list of more than 100 colors. It selects a palette of 8 but might not use all of them.

The background consists of a single color at the back and then one channel (either r, g, b) of the same color iterating from 0 to 255 while also iterating over a number of pixels within a border, all fixed to a pixel grid of variable size. The iteration over pixel numbers means the background produces very different patterns at different screen sizes

If you want to know more about the variables used they are output in the console log

Responsive to screen size. Larger resolutions will implement more brush strokes.

Some renders may be slower due to more complex collision detection in some brush settings.

Press “s” to save the image as a png.

metadata.name: Organicon, variation I #445
metadata.description:
Generative art by Frederik Vanhoutte, @wblut
A unique generator creating an endless sequence of iterations with fixed features

Organicon, variation I is a slow piece, meant to build on the screen. Warning: the preview thumbnail is a pale shadow of live view.

Interface: a first mouse click clears the screen, creates an new iteration and enables active mode. In active mode each iteration remains on screen for a limited amount of time before being replaced by the next. A second mouse click disables active mode. In active mode a small dot is displayed in the lower right corner. '+' and '-' zoom in and out.

metadata.name: 🌱 Potted & Printed #556
metadata.description:
Note:
This token is CPU intensive and may take long to render. 

---

Description:
Potted & Printed is a series of generative potted plants. There are 7 species and they have been selected from my very many indoor plants at home. The species are: 
- Snake Plant
- Monstera Adonsonii
- Alocasia
- Bird's Nest Fern
- False Shamrock
- Ponytail Palm
- Parlor Palm

---

Saving:
To save a 3500x3500 PNG file, double click/tap or press 's' 

---

Made by Sam Tsao (@sam___tsao) with p5.js

's' key save hi-res .png

metadata.name: White Night Vol.1 #91
metadata.description:
I have a long-term photography project called “White Night”, which explores special images of trees through black and white inversion.

I attempt to generate similar images by code, and this is the start of the journey.

Made with p5js.

Controls:
- Press “f” to toggle the frame, there is my signature on the mat inside the frame.
- Press “s” to save the image displayed at that moment as a PNG file.
- Change the canvas size by adding “size” URL parameter, for example: &size=1000 (you may add this and lower the number if your device can’t render properly)

metadata.name: Forest Sunrise #17
metadata.description:
A forest at sunrise can be a magical place. Rays from the sun can stream through the trees and reveal interesting patterns in the air and on the forest floor. Mist can lend an atmosphere of mystery.

In this 100% generative work I wanted to depict this type of scene. It's also my first animated art. I wanted to experiment with slow subtle animation and I think the birds and mist bring the work to life.

Primary Features:
Birds : Low, Medium, High
Sky : Red, Blue (with variations)
Fog Level : Low, Medium, High, Very High
Fog Direction : Right, Left

metadata.name: Planetary Abstracts #209
metadata.description:
A hazy planet looms large in an alien solar system. The image is "drawn" over 1,000 iterations with colored pencils on textured paper. The final image takes about 40-50 seconds.

The image size is 1200x1200. Press 's' to save a screenshot or 'p' to pause and resume drawing.

Common features:
- 50 color palettes
- Planet size, full view to partial
- 3 to 8 moons
- 2 noise methods
- 4 color modes
- 3 focus areas (line thickness)
- Vertical or horizontal accent bars

Uncommon
- Monochrome color palette
- Mono with color highlights
- Mono with gold highlights

Rare
- Mono with dark background
